Club - Create Your Meetup Page on D57 Toastmasters - Clubs Meetup Group by September 30th

This incentive is to get everyone moved to the consolidated "D57 Toastmasters - Clubs Meetup Group" of Oakland, CA. There's a $5 one-time award to make this happen for your club by September 30, 2025.

1. Fill out the form at d57tm.org/meetup or Work with Sree Gudreddi to get your VPPR access to the "D57 Toastmasters - Clubs Meeting Group" of Oakland, CA"

Talk Up Toastmasters - Send A Success Story to PRM  By January 21

Great speeches start with great stories, and every Toastmaster has a unique journey worth sharing. As part of the Talk Up Toastmasters Campaign, we’re inviting members of District 57 to share their inspiring stories about why you love Toastmasters and how it has transformed your life. Whether it’s about your first speech, a breakthrough moment, or how Toastmasters has shaped your personal or professional growth, your story can motivate others to begin their own Toastmasters journey.

Exciting Incentives:

$25 for the Best Story submitted by the deadline.
Featured Spot for the winner on the Speak, Lead, and Grow Podcast!
$5 for the First 5 Stories received.
OTMA Points for all stories that are published.
Don’t wait! The deadline is January 21—just two weeks away. Submit your story today and seize this opportunity to showcase your journey while helping us inspire others to discover the power of Toastmasters. Email your story to prm@d57tm.org by January 21 to participate. Let’s celebrate your Toastmasters journey and Talk Up Toastmasters together!

The New-club Mentor is the primary contact with a newly chartered club to help guide them as they learn about Toastmasters.

1. Be assigned by the CGD as a New-club mentor.
2. Regularly attend the meetings of a newly chartered club for a period of 6 months from the charter date.
3. To receive credit the Club President or other Club Officer must send an email to the Club Growth Director telling them that the New-club Mentor has fulfilled their role.
4. If the role is assigned after Jan 1, then the service continues into the next program year and is credited when 6 mos has elapsed.
